node.text:
As I continue to seek a deeper level of self awareness my therapy sessions have been key to me understanding the “why” behind a lot of my decision making in relationships over the years. In my most recent session with @love_mcpherson we spoke about many failed relationships of my past and how those experiences shaped me today.
-
I’ve known for some time now that when the idea of love gets to close I find a way to sabotage it. It has been my go-to mechanism to prevent being hurt. For years I created scenarios of why relationships would not be successful. Often reducing the breakdown of a potential union with me being “to busy” or telling myself “no man wants to be with a woman with a child.”
-
I isolated myself within my own thoughts that for years I committed to the idea of never having anymore children and be content with being a longterm girlfriend. Just in case I had to jump ship, there would be no lasting commitments. I’ve had quite a few amazing men come into my life and it’s seems the better we fit the more extreme my ways of sabotage grew.
-
Love is hard to accept when you don’t recognize it within yourself. And with no solid examples of what love was. I now understand why what I accepted as love in the past was nothing close.
-
I spent years telling myself I was unlovable so much so for an extended period in my life it is what I truly believed. This process of unpacking trauma and examining why it affects both my platonic and romantic relationships today has been both painful and freeing.
-
Giving myself room to exist in both hurt and healed spaces has been my biggest flex. Through that duality I’ve accepted my past self and welcome the future me who is not only worthy of love but is capable of giving it as well.

node.text:
Hey babe! I’ve been MIA for awhile now! Work has been calling like never before. Plus I’ve been working on some new content for you 🥲
-
If you follow my Instagram stories many of you know I’ve been in the kitchen getting my eating habits back in order. Sometimes I over indulge and when I do I pay for it on the scale. 
-
I have a real sweet tooth and over the holiday I wanted to indulge but I didn’t want the added bulge 🥴 So I remixed one of my favorite treats; sweet potato pie, and I turned it into a smoothie!
-
Truth be told this was quite a struggle for me but I had so much fun making this video with my good friend @mannequinskin I had to show you guys the final product 🤣 I do hope you enjoy. Drop some smoothie or food ideas you’d like to see me try next! 
-
If you’d like to try this smoothie here’s the ingredients below: 

Peach Cobbler Smoothie: Yields 12 oz
1 Cup Frozen Peaches
1 Cup Oat Milk
1/4 Cup Old Fashion Oats
1/2 Tsp Cinnamon (Ceylon is best)
1/4 Tsp Nutmeg 
1/4 Tsp Vanilla
1 1/4 Tsp Honey (Raw is best)

node.title: How Not To Make A Smoothie 🥴

node.text:
I’m super excited to share with you our newest edition to JSCULPT’s line of products. I wanted to give you guys something a little different this year and I honestly couldn’t wait for holidays to arrive to finally share with you.
-
Say hello to DEUCE, a 2-in-1 cross body gym bag.
-
YES! You read it right! You can wear DEUCE as a stylish cross body bag to carry your essentials; or, with one complete unzip & stretch DEUCE transforms into a full-sized gym bag.
-
Place your sneakers & workout favs in your bag or use it as the perfect carry-on for travel.
-
DEUCE has so much room to store your must haves and the functionality is unmatched.
-
Super light weight and easy to use. DEUCE is your new go-to everyday bag!
-
DEUCE 2-in-1 cross body gym bag is available in black & pink.
-
PLUS, If you purchase today through Monday you’ll receive a free protein shake bottle w/ your purchase.
-
I can’t wait to see how you guys rock DUECE!! Happy Holidays!

node.text:
With 52 days left in 2020 I’m sure we’ll soon see memes circulating about who can’t come with you in 2021. While we often get a kick out of these post it’s laced in truth.
-
As I dive deeper into my own self discovery I often find myself evaluating past and present relationships. Specifically weighing their importance on my life; especially my future.
- 
In the past, relationships would die and I would be so sad. I’d carry a lot of guilt blaming myself for the demise of the our relationship. Taking full ownership in why it ended. Surly I was to blame for it crumbling right?
-
Never once did I allow myself the grace of knowing perhaps their reason for being here was to learn a lesson. That lesson was learned and now it’s time to move on.
-
Where I should have thanked them for our time I maintained a negative internal dialogue because placing blame on myself was easier than accepting our season together had reached its peak.
-
I didn’t realize the many layers of codependency I carried with me until I began regular therapy sessions with @love_mcpherson 
-
The empathetic side of me wanted to hold on to these relationships simply because they existed. Even if that meant their current place left me feeling depleted.
-
I’m loyal to a fault; often overlooking my needs because I wanted to be accepted. I wanted to badly for outward appearances to show that there are other people who accept me. “Just look at all the friends I have!”
-
Not because they added true value to my life, but because I’ve attached my emotions to the idea of what that relationship should be instead of seeing it for what it is. This has proven to be a detriment to my personal growth.
-
I’m proud to say I’m creating strong roots within my personal life. But a great deal of this growth is due in part to me cutting a lot of dead leaves.
-
Are you at this place in your life? Look at the people around you; no matter how wide their branches spread within your life are the leaves dead? Do you allow them to stay simply because they were once green?
-
As we know, leaves die and bloom by the season. Pay attention to your season.

node.text:
I think I may have found my new favorite pair of jeans. The  @milanodirouge Harlow jeans exceeded my expectations!
-
Y’all know how much I love jeans!Finding jeans that I don’t have to get tailored around my waist brings a tear to my eye 🥺
-
Here are the deets:
-
4 way stretching (aka super stretchy all all around).
-
Elastic tabs are featured inside the jean for you to instantly chinch your waist! This was feature is what will forever make me seek this brand for my jeans moving forward.
-
Although the jean is stretchy its also structured so it gives a great shape WITHOUT squishing the cheeks 🍑 which is A-1.
-
I’m wearing a size 31. I’m not really sure what size that correlates to but I’m usually a size 11/12. Definitely take your own measurements just to be sure.
-
Congrats to @iammilanrouge for taking time to create the perfect jean! Chefs kisses Queen 👑

node.title: THE PERFECT JEAN! @milanodirouge Harlow Jean Is IT!

node.text:
One thing about me, I’m gone get some help! 
-
As many of you know, I am an advocate for therapy. As a woman who’s battled depression I know first hand the freedom that comes from experiencing this.
-
In my latest session I spoke with my therapist about my “why” in searching for a partner. What are my needs for the long term? Not for the present. We uncovered so much. But my greatest take-a-way was this piece here.
-
Did you know your partner will only fulfill 10% of your needs? You are still responsible for 90% of your happiness!
-
Watch, think about it and then let’s chat. I’d honestly love to hear your opinion on this topic.
-
Thank you @love_mcpherson for your insight!

node.title: Love Will Not Solve My Problems

node.text:
But did you workout today?
-
I’m chipping away daily at my fitness goals. Right now I’m just focusing on consistency (SHOWING UP) and increasing my cardio 💦 
-
I switched out my old original @jsculptfitness belt for the Logo Mania reverse! I’ve been rocking it because it’s a 2-n-1 reversible belt that I can wear to the gym. But after, I can remove the band and wear it underneath my clothes if I wanted! 
- 
We’re kicking off our 4th Of July sale with 20% off all reversible belts 7/2-7/5. If you purchase during our sale you’ll receive 20% off PLUS FREE SHIPPING and a protein shake bottle free with your purchase
-
We also just extended our sizes! We now offer XS-8X and all sizes are in stock and ready to ship 📦 No code needed at checkout!

node.text:
What’s something you’re proud of? I have quite a few but nothing tops this ⭐️
-
July of this year I’ll celebrating my 4th year of business with @jsculptfitness 
-
In 2017 I had no clue what I’d be stepping into. What started as me documenting my own journey of weight loss & depression would eventually grow into community of women that would share similar experiences of personal development. We’d share our struggles and our wins navigating through life. 
-
While on my weight loss journey I enjoyed wearing various belts designed to be worn at the gym. I was ready for a major pivot in my life and career so I finally decided to launch my own product to provide an alternative to what was currently available on the market. It was a major turning point in my life. An idea I had for some time I’m glad I took the chance. And it didn’t hurt the in my second attempt at business ownership I’d finally experienced some success. It felt like every moment leading up to this point was preparing me for the brand. 
-
I’m thankful for the wins. And even more grateful for the many lessons. Despite the many challenges I’ve faced with running this brand there’s not much I would change. I’ve learned that mishaps are just opportunities for correction.
